t of hazardous manufacturing to developing countries, and the current "greenwashing" of viscose as an eco-friendly product. Deeply researched and boldly presented, this book brings to light an industrial hazard whose egregious history ranks with those of asbestos, lead, and mercury.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aRayonxHistory. 0aViscose processxHistory. 7aTechnology & Engineering / Materials Science / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2014-2016z978311053800740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300224887423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300224887.jpg  a978-3-11-053800-7  YUP eBook Package 2014-2016c2014d2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles